\begin_layout Standard
This suggestion together with the comments of referee 2 on the accuracy
 and speed of these pseudopotentials led us to use our methods to much larger
 systems than the one studied in the original version as well as to distorted
 systems.
 We have chosen two examples, which we believe address these points: a coronene
 molecule embedded in a carbon nanotube and increasingly large helicenes.
 The first example shows that despite the fact accuracy that of our method
 does not reach chemical accuracy in the case of highly energetical excited
 states (ionisation potential being the paragon of electronic excitation)
 it can be useful to determine chemical properties in large systems.
 The second example, shows that this method can help to solve highly difficult
 assignations (the determination of absolute configuration of helicenes
 is not a trivial task) in a limited time, especially if combined with highly
 efficient semi empirical approaches like the sTDA of Grimme and coworkers.
\end_layout

